message.content:
Before Cam broke his right arm, he could type 9 words per minute on his phone. Therefore, in 5 minutes, he could type:

5 minutes/60 seconds * (9 words/minute) = 45 words/minute

After Cam broke his arm and had to use his left hand for a while, he could only type 6 words per minute. Therefore, in 5 minutes, he could type:

5 minutes/60 seconds * (6 words/minute) = 30 words/minute

The difference between the number of words Cam could type in 5 minutes before and after he broke his arm is:

45 words - 30 words = 15 words
